# <PROJECT NAME> — coding agent guide

This file tells the coding agent how to work in THIS repository. Copy it to the
repo root as `CLAUDE.md` and fill in the specifics. The more accurate this is,
the better the pull requests will be.

## Stack

- Framework: <e.g. Next.js App Router 16 / React Native / etc.>
- Language: TypeScript
- Styling: <e.g. Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui>
- Data / auth: <e.g. Supabase (Auth + Postgres + RLS)>
- Hosting: <e.g. Vercel>

## Commands

- Install: `npm install`
- Dev: `npm run dev`
- Build (run before finishing): `npm run build`
- Lint: `npm run lint`
- Test: <command, or "no test suite yet">

## Conventions

- Match the existing file structure and naming; look at neighboring files first.
- Keep changes scoped to the issue being implemented — no unrelated refactors.
- Every new page must be responsive (mobile 393px through desktop).
- Do not add new dependencies unless the issue requires it.
- Do not touch environment variables, secrets, or CI config.
- Do not run destructive commands or delete data.

## Definition of done

- The change satisfies every acceptance criterion in the issue.
- `npm run build` passes.
- The PR description explains what changed and lists anything left for a human
  (e.g. "final legal copy to be provided by the client").
